@startuml Tapping Modes State Machine
!theme plain
title Tapping Modes - State Machine\n6 Modes for Automated Tap Reversal

[*] --> MODE_OFF

state "MODE 0: OFF\nNormal Drilling" as MODE_OFF {
  MODE_OFF : No auto-reversal
  MODE_OFF : Manual control only
}

state "MODE 1: PEDAL\nFoot Pedal Trigger" as MODE_PEDAL {
  state "Waiting" as P_WAIT
  state "Tapping" as P_TAP
  state "Reversing" as P_REV

  P_WAIT --> P_TAP : Foot pedal pressed\n(PC3 = LOW)
  P_TAP --> P_REV : Foot pedal released\n(PC3 = HIGH)
  P_REV --> P_WAIT : Quill returns to top

  note right of P_TAP
    Forward while pedal down
    Reverse when released
    User controls timing
  end note
}

state "MODE 2: SMART\nQuill Direction" as MODE_SMART {
  state "Descending" as S_DESC
  state "Ascending" as S_ASC

  S_DESC --> S_ASC : Quill direction reversed\n(depth decreasing)
  S_ASC --> S_DESC : Quill descending again

  note right of S_DESC
    Motor forward while descending
    Auto-reverse when ascending
    Follows quill movement
  end note
}

state "MODE 3: DEPTH\nTarget Depth" as MODE_DEPTH {
  state "Drilling" as D_DRILL
  state "At Depth" as D_DEPTH
  state "Retracting" as D_RET

  D_DRILL --> D_DEPTH : Depth ≥ target
  D_DEPTH --> D_RET : Auto-reverse
  D_RET --> D_DRILL : Quill at top

  note right of D_DRILL
    Forward to target depth
    Reverse when reached
    Configurable depth setting
  end note
}

state "MODE 4: LOAD\nCV Overshoot Detection" as MODE_LOAD {
  state "In Material" as L_MAT
  state "Through Hole" as L_THRU
  state "Reversing" as L_REV

  L_MAT --> L_THRU : CV ≥ 130% of target
  note right
    CV overshoot indicates
    tap exited material
    (through-hole detected)
  end note

  L_THRU --> L_REV : CV burst confirms\n(3× rapid CV queries)
  L_REV --> L_MAT : Quill at top

  note right of L_THRU
    **Phase 2.3: Jam Detection**

    Uses jam.c module
    for load monitoring
  end note
}

state "MODE 5: PECK\nTimed Cycles" as MODE_PECK {
  state "Peck Forward" as PK_FWD
  state "Peck Reverse" as PK_REV
  state "Dwell" as PK_DWELL

  PK_FWD --> PK_REV : Timer expires
  note right: Configurable forward time
  PK_REV --> PK_DWELL : Timer expires
  note right: Configurable reverse time
  PK_DWELL --> PK_FWD : Dwell complete
  note right: Configurable dwell time

  note right of PK_FWD
    Rapid peck cycles
    Stresses queues
    (10ms queue timeout
    for responsiveness)
  end note
}

MODE_OFF --> MODE_PEDAL : TAP 1
MODE_OFF --> MODE_SMART : TAP 2
MODE_OFF --> MODE_DEPTH : TAP 3
MODE_OFF --> MODE_LOAD : TAP 4
MODE_OFF --> MODE_PECK : TAP 5

MODE_PEDAL --> MODE_OFF : TAP 0
MODE_SMART --> MODE_OFF : TAP 0
MODE_DEPTH --> MODE_OFF : TAP 0
MODE_LOAD --> MODE_OFF : TAP 0
MODE_PECK --> MODE_OFF : TAP 0

note bottom
  **Tapping Task (20Hz, Priority 3)**

  Monitors:
  • Quill depth (from task_depth via g_state)
  • Motor status (motor_running from g_state)
  • Foot pedal (PC3 GPIO)
  • CV (actual motor speed from MCB)

  Commands Motor via:
  • MOTOR_CMD(CMD_MOTOR_TAP_FORWARD)
  • MOTOR_CMD(CMD_MOTOR_TAP_REVERSE)
  • MOTOR_CMD(CMD_MOTOR_STOP)

  All commands checked for queue overflow (Phase 1.2)
  Emergency stop if motor queue full
end note

note right of MODE_LOAD
  **CV Burst Pattern**
  (discovered 2026-01-25)

  Before reversal:
  1. Detect CV > 130% target
  2. Query CV × 3 rapidly (50ms apart)
  3. Average readings
  4. Confirm overshoot
  5. Trigger reversal

  Prevents false triggers
end note

@enduml
